    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="495" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <head>No. 40.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Sir <persName type="to">L. S. Sackville
                                    West</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-05-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 28,
                                1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir Lionel</hi>: In regard to the inquiry
                            contained in your note of the 25th instant, relating to the British
                            vessels seized in Behring’s Sea, I should be glad to have an interview
                            with you this afternoon at 3 o’clock, should that hour be convenient for
                            you to come to the Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
